<TEXT>
a grand jury friday refused to indict a 
former smalltown police chief on murder charges in the 1978 
slaying of his wifes first husband whose body was found buried in 
the chiefs yard in march 
robert chambers 36 at this point is no longer under 
charges assistant attorney general gregory swope said in 
announcing the grand jury decision the prosecutor gave no 
explanation for the action 
chambers was arrested and charged with murder april 15 in the 
slaying of 25yearold russell bean a friend and drinking buddys 
of chambers 
chambers resigned as parttime police chief of marlow a town of 
about 600 near the massachusetts and vermont borders in the 
southwestern corner of the state after state police dug up the 
body from chambers front yard march 14 
the case is back to square one swope said its as if 
hed never been arrested and were still investigating he said 
new charges against chambers would only be warranted if there 
were some developments in the case 
i feel real fine chambers said by telephone from a friends 
home friday night he declined to answer any other questions 
police began digging up chambers yard after chambers 
relatives relaying a story told them by chambers father shortly 
before his death march 9 told authorities chambers had 
accidentally killed bean in a fight 
the relatives said that chambers father clifton told them he 
helped his son bury the body according to court papers the 
relatives said that the elder chambers 61 when he died had told 
them not to say anything until after his death 
relatives alleged in court papers that chambers and bean had 
swapped wives allegations denied by chambers current wife sylvia 
chambers 
chambers moved out of his house after beans body was found and 
his wife filed for divorce 
chambers was held at the cheshire county jail until thursday 
when three people signed over property to allow him to make bail of 
75000 cash and 75000 property 
mark sisti chambers lawyer commended prosecutors saying they 
handled the case professionally they really threw a fair shot at 
the grand jury he said 
after bean disappeared in 1978 his wife sylvia married 
chambers who had divorced his wife deborah pathologists 
determined that bean had been beaten in the head and chest 
</TEXT>
