<TEXT>
a locomotive rammed the back of an nj 
transit corp passenger train thursday and authorities said at 
least 20 people were injured one critically 
the train was waiting for a signal to cross a bridge when it was 
hit by a work engine traveling about 10 mph said rose sheridan a 
spokeswoman for nj transit 
most of the injuries were to passengers in the last of six 
passenger cars on the commuter train heading from bayhead junction 
to new york ms sheridan said 
the passengers suffered mainly neck and back injuries said ms 
sheridan 
there was no derailment she said 
nj transit investigators will interview the locomotive driver to 
determine the cause of the accident ms sheridan said 
anthony buccella 24 of point pleasant was listed in critical 
condition at south amboy memorial hospital two other passengers 
were admitted for observation and listed in good condition 
the other injured passengers were treated at hospitals and 
released 
