a man who prosecutors said was obsessed 
with a bank teller was convicted of attempted murder thursday in 
the speargun shooting of her husband 
robert w freemyer jr 31 of upper saddle river admitted 
firing the spear that hit robert jablonski in 1987 but said it was 
an accident the spear struck jablonski in the back of the head but 
left only a large bump 
authorities said freemyer plotted to murder jablonski because he 
was obsessed with jablonskis wife elizabeth 
he looked at her every day he brought strange gifts to her 
parents house he spent a month drawing a picture for a woman he 
barely knew bergen county assistant prosecutor sharyn peiffer 
argued tuesday 
defense attorney vincent w basile said jablonski was shot 
during a chance meeting with freemyer 
freemyer could receive 10 to 20 years in prison at sentencing 
basile said he will appeal 
