includes submarinelaunched missiles and bombers 
supporters of the mx say it has already been developed and would 
be much cheaper to simply build 50 more and put them on railroads 
but midgetman backers contend the mx is vulnerable to a soviet 
first strike and nuclear stability would be improved by building a 
weapon that has fewer warheads and thus is less attractive as a 
target 
