i came here specifically to buy the documents said the 
british collector who refused to give his name 
the work commissioned by the philharmonic society of london 
was first performed in vienna in 1824 
the autographed pages of music which have been recently 
authenticated include 27 bars of changes in the orchestral part of 
the ode to joy the choral last movement of the work 
sothebys said beethoven wrote down the music in his usual 
haphazard style 
the alterations are not written down in any order but are 
seemingly jotted down at random moving backwards and forwards from 
movement to movement some even added in pencil on top of earlier 
instructions said the auction house 
