nine days before he was due to take office he is not running for 
another term and the only candidate who has officially declared is 
dany chamoun a former christian militia leader 
the change in presidents is seen by the reagan administration as 
a good opportunity to seek political reform the need to stem the 
factional violence is particularly urgent for the united states in 
view of the collapse of the countrys economy which has all but 
wiped out its middle class 
the lebanese pound once the mideasts most stable currency has 
nosedived to an alltime low of 700 to the dollar until 1985 it 
was 25 to the dollar 
but a lebanese christian official suggested there is more to the 
us and syrian efforts than just a desire for calm in lebanon 
lebanon is not the main thrust said robert farah executive 
director of the lebanese information and research center in 
washington which represents a coalition of christian forces 
farah said the united states is hoping it can parlay its help 
with syrias lebanese problem into syrian support for us efforts 
to start israeliarab peace talks syria has so far rejected the 
plan 
the united states also is hoping syria can use its influence 
with the palestine liberation organization to quell a fivemonth 
uprising by palestinians in the west bank and gaza strip against 
israels occupation the us official said 
syria hopes better relations with the united states may ease 
some of its economic problems and ensure its role in future us 
diplomacy 
