should proceed to a final debate and vote in the house of commons 
britain by allowing abortions at up to 28 weeks or about seven 
months of pregnancy has one of the western worlds most liberal 
abortion laws in the united states abortions are allowed without 
regulation in the first three months of pregnancy 
after that some state regulation is allowed 
supporters of the new law argued that abortions should not be 
allowed when a fetus might have a reasonable chance to survive 
outside the womb at 24 weeks such survival is rare but survival 
at 28 weeks is estimated at 74 percent in optimal conditions the 
usual length of pregnancy is 40 weeks 
of the 172286 abortions in england and wales in 1986 the 
latest year for which statistics are available 10770 or 6 
percent were done after 17 weeks according to the department of 
health and social security 
opponents of the bill contended that an 18week limit would deny 
women the choice of abortion because of a fetal handicap since it 
might not be possible to detect the handicap at such an early stage 
of pregnancy 
fourteen previous attempts to amend the 1967 abortion act have 
failed but parliaments antiabortion lobby had gained widespread 
bipartisan support for the latest bill 
