<TEXT>
northern mexico a place of its own 
kind stretched along the us border has for years suffered a 
reputation as an untamed wilderness inhabited by barbarians 
even a regional dish the unique charcoalroasted beef called 
carne asada has been maligned 
where carne asada begins civilization ends 
so said jose vasconcelos the intellectual and mexican education 
minister in 192024 
his remark was often repeated by others 
but attitudes like these are starting to change thanks to 
northern mexicos newfound economic strength impressive cultural 
programs and electionyear politicking 
underlying the norths sudden popularity is a government attempt 
to strengthen national unity at a time when overall economic and 
political uncertainty troubles the entire country 
ive come to tell you that im proud to be of the north 
carlos salinas de gortari presidential candidate of the dominant 
institutional revolutionary party said on a campaign tour here 
words are converted into actions 
although born in mexico city the oftenscorned federal capital 
salinas de gortaris father was a northerner and the candidate has 
maintained strong ties to the north 
another reflection of the attitude change appeared in a recent 
issue of the national magazine el cotidiano for a long time the 
border was viewed as a place where the most corrosive elements of 
the nation took root denationalization provincialism barbarism 
unlimited reinforcement of the american way of life 
recent investigations have proven the fallacy of the 
generalized idea that border inhabitants are by definition 
pronorth american 
the north consists of the states of northern baja california 
sonora chihuahua coahuila nuevo leon and tamaulipas they are 
spread across 316000 square miles of mostly barren land that 
extends from the pacific ocean to the gulf of mexico thirteen 
million of mexicos 82 million people live there 
divided from each other by vast deserts and two sierra madre 
ranges and from the rest of mexico by hundreds of miles and 
different histories the isolated northerners have learned to rely 
on themselves 
their ties to the us southwest which was part of mexico until 
1848 are cultural and economic but their national identity and 
regional pride is strong 
the united states wants to analyze mexico according to 
american standards they think whatever is good for america has to 
be good for the rest of the world said mayor jaime bermudez of 
ciudad juarez a northern city 
but were different we think differently and we live 
differently 
out of a hostile environment northerners created strong 
regional economies that have helped sustain mexico for decades the 
mines of chihuahua and coahuila cattle ranches and agricultural 
fields of sonora industry and citrus of nuevo leon fishing and 
tourism in baja california oil shipping agriculture and border 
businesses in tamaulipas 
aptly nicknamed the sultan of the north the city of 
monterrey with 28 million people is the regions largest richest 
and most industrialized city 
nearer the border tijuana and ciudad juarez vying to become 
second largest with a little over a million people each are the 
two most dynamic cities in the area today this is due largely to 
investments in the maquiladora industry foreignowned assembly 
operations that produce goods at mexicos lower wages for export 
mostly to the united states 
when the economic crisis began in 1982 this zone suffered 
serious and profound uncertainty said the outgoing president 
miguel de la madrid during his most recent tour of border cities 
but with new development plans during these past few years 
the northern border has become one of the most dynamic zones in the 
country from the economic point of view 
as did previous presidents de la madrid has pumped hundreds of 
millions of pesos into the north much of it for sewers roads 
electricity water and other necessities 
but government funding has been targeted in recent years for 
cultural centers museums libraries and city beautification 
projects like parks and plazas 
the emphasis on northern cultural development which started 
about five years ago stemmed from a mistaken belief in mexico city 
that the border states needed to be rescued from a us cultural 
invasion said jorge bustamante director of the tijuanabased 
northern border college 
nevertheless such cultural programs as a firstever arts 
festival in sonora last year forums on border issues and a new 
magazine called cultura norte are giving northerners opportunities 
to express their unique art forms 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP880506-0242 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
and inevitably the uncultured provincial hicks tag is 
fading away while regional pride is strengthened 
weve always resented the fact that the north was paying taxes 
and everything went to mexico city said mayor bermudez 
but now the government sees the monster it created in mexico 
city it has finally realized that we are producing things and 
its investing here meanwhile northern mexicos maquiladora 
industry is becoming more and more crucial to national efforts to 
ride out the severe economic crisis that has plagued the country 
for six years 
shunned as secondclass operations when they started in the 
mid1960s the maquiladoras now vie with tourism as the no 2 
source of foreign income for mexico after oil 
more than 330000 people worked in 1400 maquildaoras last year 
while the industry brought in more than 14 billion in revenues 
and new plants are opening up throughout the north 
nowadays the opportunities are more in the north this is the 
land of opportunity said jorge juarez manager of a maquiladora 
in ciudad juarez 
one result has been higher education levels and incomes in the 
north than national averages uemployment generally is lower 
still northern mexico has problems 
inflation and the cost of living in the largely dollarbased 
societies usually run higher than the national average up to 25 
percent higher right on the border 
the north is a new frontier for people fleeing the chaos caused 
by overpopulation pollution and earth tremors of mexico city the 
poverty of mexicos indigenous south and the boredom of life on 
sparse communal farms 
its a way station for illegal immigrants on their way to the 
united states and the drain on limited public services is showing 
crime and drug addiction are rising housing is in short supply 
in the cities farmers are clamoring for increases in the 
guaranteed prices for their products 
even with that however northern mexico still gains new 
respect not only because of its increasing economic power but also 
because of candidate salinas de gortaris emphasis on his northern 
heritage and what his party calls his northern qualities 
northerners always have had to fend for themselves said 
romeo flores caballero a federal congressman from nuevo leon 
where salinas de gortaris father was born that produced a 
independent breed of people known for their sincerity work ethics 
and frankness 
salinas de gortari definitely has those qualities 
northern mexico however is a stronghold of the opposition 
national action party and its presidential candidate is wooing 
voters with a promise of cleaning up corruption long a sore spot 
with northerners 
meanwhile the third major presidential candidate cuauhtemoc 
cardenas has drawn huge crowds in the north specifically in 
coahuilas laguna region 
farmers there remember cardenas father the late president 
lazaro cardenas for his agrarian reform program that gave them 
land 
while other mexicans are looking northward with new respect 
these days northerners are looking southward mindful of the 
distant past 
hector manuel gallego the rector of the university of baja 
california alluded to that in his book northern mexico 
historical vision of the border 
if the abrupt mountains and the sizzling deserts have 
separated those in the different regions of the border the 
knowledge of a shared past brings us together he wrote 
what geography has separated history unites 
</TEXT>
