<TEXT>
coleco industries inc the company 
that rocketed to superstardom with its cabbage patch kids dolls 
may need another miracle to recover from its current financial 
problems 
unless it can restructure its 335 million debt and raise 
working capital coleco could soon wind up in bankruptcy court 
seeking protection from its creditors said morton e handel who 
was named this week to replace arnold c greenberg as chairman and 
chief executive officer 
i see myself under a very tight time deadline measured in 
days or weeks in order to be able to resolve the problems 
currently facing us said handel 53 a 14year coleco veteran 
and most recently the head of finances and investor relations 
were zealously trying to find some sources of working capital 
in order to give us the opportunity to run the company and bring it 
back to the point of profitability and viability he said in an 
interview 
the company has proposed that investors who own its bonds 
exchange those securities for 6 million shares of coleco stock and 
new bonds worth 119 million 
the company is in default on the interest payments on its 335 
million in debt and has set a deadline of may 13 for the exchange 
coleco has also hired clevelandbased hallwood group inc to help 
it restructure its finances 
somebody obviously has a great sense of black humor since its 
friday the 13th david leibowitz senior vice president of 
american securities corp in new york said friday 
in an effort to cut costs coleco this week laid off 475 workers 
45 percent of its total us work force mostly at its three 
manufacturing plants in the albany ny area that left it with 
about 580 employees in the united states compared with an average 
of 2500 in 1987 
colecos other products include alf dolls big wheels plastic 
tricycles and board games such as scrabble and trivial pursuit 
industry sources say the company holds about 5 percent of the 
nations toy market 
leibowitz and other analysts said the same aggressive management 
style that helped coleco hit the jackpot with the gamble on cabbage 
patch kids dolls in 1983 helped bring on the current woes 
the dolls which were introduced in 1983 after a number of other 
toy companies rejected the product helped coleco end 1985 in its 
strongest financial condition ever with sales of 776 million and 
record earnings of 64 million 
what went wrong the company was just too aggressively run 
said paul valentine an analyst with standard amp poors corp they 
bet the ranch basically and lost they waited until it was too late 
to address their inflated costs and shore up their finances 
valentine said he didnt blame greenberg or any particular 
product line such as the toys based on the rambo movie character 
or the troubled adam home computer rather colecos woes stem from 
a financial approach common in the toy industry he said 
they didnt cut their costs quickly enough after sales of the 
cabbage patch dolls fell off sharply he said like many toy 
companies coleco had a cost structure which assumed only the 
greatest success for the companys products 
the company which became coleco industries in 1961 has faced 
tough times before it entered the snowmobile business in 1972 but 
snowfalls were light for the next three years the economy was 
depressed and losses were heavy 
the company posted a 22 million loss in 1978 threatening its 
survival in 1980 the securities and exchange commission charged 
coleco with misstating its financial results to mask troubles 
in 1982 the company began a move toward prosperity with the 
introduction of its colecovision home video game system the 
company saw its future in electronics and in 1983 unveiled its 
600 adam home computer 
adam was a monumental flop while sales of colecovision cooled 
the company lost 798 million in 1984 despite 540 million in 
sales of cabbage patch kids 
valentine said he doesnt believe coleco will have to file under 
chapter 11 of the us bankruptcy code saying investors have 
appeared more willing in recent weeks to consummate the exchange 
he also predicted coleco may sell off a toy line to raise some cash 
if it can weather the current storm leibowitz said coleco has a 
strong enough product line to remain an industry leader 
this is a company that has a strong pedigree in the business 
and one is not going to write them off as a meaningful player in 
the trade he said what we are saying is the overwhelming 
consideration and the major concern right now is simply the ability 
to keep the doors open and work out an accommodation 
</TEXT>
