company is incorporated in delaware 
the proposed settlement which still must be approved by the 
court would add 924 million to the cost of the recapitalization 
the investor group pursuing a 2 billion takeover bid desert 
partners lp of midland texas said in a statement it did not 
believe the settlement would be approved 
shareholders objected to aspects of the recapitalization plan 
that would dilute the value of their shares usg spokeswoman randi 
killian said 
under its initial plan usg proposed to pay shareholders 37 in 
cash debentures with a face value of 5 and a share of stock in 
the recapitalized corporation for each common share 
but each of the 22 million shares held by the companys 
employee investment plans instead were to be swapped for eight 
shares in the new company usg would have had to issue 179 million 
new shares to the investment plans which irked some shareholders 
over dilution of their holdings 
as part of its proposed settlement usg agreed the shares held 
by the employee plans would receive the same payout of cash notes 
and stock as other sharesholders rather than just straight stock 
the settlement proposal would keep the number of outstanding 
shares at 54 million down from the 70 million called for under the 
original plan 
it is now costing usg more but the shares are worth more 
because there are fewer outstanding killian said 
